---
title: Aubergine Gnocchi Gratin with Baby Spinach and Rocket Salad
description: If you’re a pasta lover looking for something a little bit different, this gnocchi gratin is the perfect solution. These versatile Italian potato dumplings can be cooked a number of different ways but for this recipe we’ve gone for a double whammy, pan-frying them to give them a crispy coat before baking them in a rich aubergine and tomato sauce. Topped with a golden cheesy crumb and served with a simple rocket salad, this really is Mediterranean comfort cooking at its best.
